he dedicated his entire being

27:33.060 --> 27:36.545
to this island,
and now that's my job.

27:36.547 --> 27:38.380
- Hmm.

27:38.399 --> 27:41.992
But you miss him, though?
- My great uncle?

27:42.144 --> 27:44.828
Yeah, of course.
He was a very wise man.

27:44.980 --> 27:47.572
- No, James.

27:47.649 --> 27:50.650
<i> [soft music]</i>

27:50.728 --> 27:52.152
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

27:52.171 --> 27:55.339
- Yeah. Every day.

27:57.325 --> 27:59.826
- Elena,

27:59.904 --> 28:02.070
you just girl-talked!

28:02.072 --> 28:04.831
- I did?
- Well done.

28:04.909 --> 28:07.409
[laughter]
- Yeah!

28:07.428 --> 28:10.312
[laughter]

28:13.083 --> 28:15.100
- Bartender had a heavy pour.

28:15.177 --> 28:16.694
[laughs]
- Yeah, I got you, honey.

28:19.532 --> 28:22.199
- Thank you so much.

28:22.350 --> 28:24.927
- Bitch.

28:24.945 --> 28:26.428
- Netty, wait.
- What's wrong with you?

28:26.521 --> 28:28.688
- We just saw you coming
out of Tristan's room.

28:28.708 --> 28:30.648
What--
- No. No, no, no, Netty--

28:30.801 --> 28:31.858
- After all I've been through,

28:31.936 --> 28:34.044
I finally find
a teeny bit of happiness,

28:34.196 --> 28:36.121
and why are you deliberately
trying to hurt me?

28:36.273 --> 28:39.049
- Netty, please, can you just
entertain the concept

28:39.201 --> 28:41.610
that not everything
is about you?

28:41.612 --> 28:43.962
- Oh, oh, Netty,
you should hear her out.

28:44.114 --> 28:45.556
This is important.
- No, I'm done.

28:45.707 --> 28:46.706
- Ladies, good evening.

28:46.784 --> 28:48.283
I regret to inform you

28:48.302 --> 28:51.286
that we have a "no fighting
after 9:00 p.m." policy.

28:51.305 --> 28:53.455
- That's fine.
I'm going to bed.

28:53.474 --> 28:55.640
- No, not yet, I'm afraid.
Stand there, please.

28:55.793 --> 28:57.809
Thank you.

28:57.962 --> 28:59.628
<i> [tense music]</i>

28:59.630 --> 29:01.296
It's a shame
to see you like this

29:01.315 --> 29:04.649
when you have so little time
left with each other.

29:04.802 --> 29:08.061
- What do you mean?

29:08.138 --> 29:10.655
What the hell is this?

29:10.808 --> 29:12.249
Roarke?

29:12.400 --> 29:14.476
- She said that we only have
a little bit of time

29:14.478 --> 29:15.994
with each other.

29:16.071 --> 29:17.980
Do you think that's one of us?

29:17.998 --> 29:20.315
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:20.408 --> 29:23.594
- It's me.
It's me, isn't it?

29:23.745 --> 29:26.412
- Why would you think that?
- Just open it.

29:26.432 --> 29:27.765
Go open it.

29:27.841 --> 29:29.916
- Netty, come help.

29:30.010 --> 29:37.274
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:38.352 --> 29:39.693
- [gasps]

29:46.176 --> 29:47.843
- Well, you said
you wanted rest.

29:47.861 --> 29:50.496
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

29:54.794 --> 29:57.795
- It's me.
I'm still young.

29:57.797 --> 30:00.856
<i> [soft music]</i>

30:00.858 --> 30:04.617
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:04.637 --> 30:06.028
- Is that me?

30:06.046 --> 30:09.122
- I look weird.
Why do I look so weird?

30:09.216 --> 30:11.791
- Seems the poster child
for self-actualization

30:11.811 --> 30:13.535
went a little overboard
on the filler.

30:13.537 --> 30:14.978
Gee, I wonder
who the surgeon was.

30:15.055 --> 30:17.389
- Oh, look, you're with Paul.

30:17.541 --> 30:19.224
Seems defining yourself
by someone

30:19.301 --> 30:22.468
other than the man you're with
isn't as easy as it seems.

30:22.488 --> 30:24.137
- I don't do that.

30:24.139 --> 30:27.566
We probably just came together.

30:27.642 --> 30:29.051
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

30:29.053 --> 30:30.327
- Looks pretty cozy to me.

30:30.404 --> 30:31.720
- Well, it beats dying alone
with my cat.

30:31.722 --> 30:33.905
- At least my cat
isn't sleeping with a skank

30:33.982 --> 30:35.407
who lives on a houseboat.

30:35.501 --> 30:38.060
- Just shut up!

30:38.078 --> 30:39.652
I'm dead!

30:39.730 --> 30:42.172
You guys can't stop arguing
for five seconds.

30:42.324 --> 30:44.566
It's been like this
since high school.

30:44.568 --> 30:46.844
I'm tired
of being your mediator.

30:46.995 --> 30:50.222
You two are
your own problem now.

30:52.518 --> 30:59.398
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

31:02.862 --> 31:07.347
I can't be here.

31:07.366 --> 31:09.107
Was that real?

31:09.184 --> 31:12.852
- As of this moment, yeah.
- Well, change it.

31:12.930 --> 31:15.205
I can't leave my kids
without a mom.

31:15.357 --> 31:17.449
And I don't want to die.
Okay, please.

31:17.601 --> 31:20.860
I will do anything.
- It's not up to me, Margot.

31:20.938 --> 31:23.213
Remember, I just
lay the chessboard.

31:23.290 --> 31:26.124
Your fate is entirely
in your hands.

31:26.201 --> 31:28.960
You came to Fantasy Island
looking for the time

31:29.054 --> 31:31.463
and the space to rest,

31:31.539 --> 31:33.448
and you're barely
taking advantage of that.

31:33.467 --> 31:36.542
- Well, my friends needed me.
- Did they?

31:36.562 --> 31:39.638
- Yes, yes.
They have since high school.

31:39.714 --> 31:41.640
- And if you were to just
leave them alone

31:41.716 --> 31:44.067
and take care of your own needs
for a while,

31:44.144 --> 31:46.052
what are you afraid
would happen?

31:46.130 --> 31:48.797
- I don't know,
but they would implode.

31:48.799 --> 31:49.981
- And you feel that way

31:50.058 --> 31:52.242
about every single obligation
in your life?

31:56.582 --> 31:59.808
- Maybe.

31:59.826 --> 32:02.811
How do I die?

32:02.813 --> 32:05.163
- I don't know exactly.

32:05.315 --> 32:08.150
I assume that you
neglect yourself

32:08.152 --> 32:10.243
in order to make
other people happy,

32:10.262 --> 32:12.578
which is a--
it's a lovely characteristic.

32:12.656 --> 32:15.490
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:15.509 --> 32:17.768
- Until it isn't.

32:17.919 --> 32:19.937
- Yeah.

32:20.013 --> 32:22.998
<i> [smooth music]</i>

32:23.016 --> 32:28.761
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:28.781 --> 32:30.763
- Mm-hmm, I know this one.

32:30.841 --> 32:35.010
- Oh, I like a girl with
a sophisticated taste in music.

32:35.012 --> 32:38.680
- Well, I grew up
in a musical family,

32:38.682 --> 32:41.016
so--but how about you?

32:41.018 --> 32:44.110
- I'm just an old soul,
I guess.

32:44.129 --> 32:46.204
Now, they don't make them
like this anymore.

32:46.356 --> 32:49.524
- Mm-mm.
[laughs]

32:49.543 --> 32:56.431
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

32:58.960 --> 33:03.313
- You know, do you think
I upset Elena before,

33:03.390 --> 33:06.558
you know, asking about James?

33:06.634 --> 33:07.892
- She can handle it.

33:08.045 --> 33:10.378
You know, I've known Elena
for a long time,

33:10.397 --> 33:13.064
and you being here
has been really good for her.

33:13.217 --> 33:14.640
- Really?
- Yeah.

33:14.660 --> 33:17.569
You know, when she called me up
to come here for girls' night,

33:17.645 --> 33:19.312
I thought she was
messing with me.

33:19.331 --> 33:21.981
- You know, I didn't think she
would agree to it, honestly.

33:22.059 --> 33:24.650
- [laughing]
That's what I mean.

33:24.670 --> 33:27.487
You've been a great influence
on her, Ruby,

33:27.564 --> 33:29.655
and on all of us.

33:29.657 --> 33:31.824
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

33:31.902 --> 33:34.252
- Thank you.

33:34.329 --> 33:38.423
- So what do you want
to do now?

33:38.500 --> 33:42.911
We could put Segundo's hand
in a bowl of warm water.

33:42.929 --> 33:45.764
[both laugh]

33:45.916 --> 33:49.934
- As tempting as that is,

33:50.087 --> 33:52.178
I'd like to keep dancing.

33:52.197 --> 33:55.515
I mean, if you do.

33:55.534 --> 33:58.326
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:07.287 --> 34:11.864
- Why did you think
it was you in the casket?

34:11.942 --> 34:14.867
- Forget it.

34:14.945 --> 34:16.127
- Is there something wrong?

34:16.204 --> 34:19.705
Is that why you wanted
a different body?

34:19.800 --> 34:21.707
- I thought it came back.

34:21.802 --> 34:24.877
- Thought what came back?

34:24.955 --> 34:27.046
- Netty, I didn't go
see Tristan

34:27.066 --> 34:31.793
because I wanted
to sleep with him.

34:31.795 --> 34:33.719
I was hoping he could help me.

34:33.797 --> 34:37.240
- Help you with what?

34:39.078 --> 34:42.412
- I had cancer, Nette.

34:42.564 --> 34:45.415
<i> [somber music]</i>

34:45.567 --> 34:47.459
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

34:50.831 --> 34:53.739
- You had cancer?

34:53.759 --> 34:57.094
When?
Are you okay?

34:57.170 --> 34:58.987
Why am I just hearing
about this now?

34:59.005 --> 35:00.672
- No, I'm fine.

35:00.766 --> 35:03.082
They caught it with surgery,

35:03.102 --> 35:06.269
except they screwed up
on the reconstruction part,

35:06.421 --> 35:09.556
and now I need more surgery.

35:09.591 --> 35:12.216
I tried to tell you, though.
I did.

35:12.294 --> 35:14.853
But you were going through
your divorce when we talked,

35:15.005 --> 35:18.189
and you never let me
get a word in.

35:18.342 --> 35:20.766
- So you didn't tell me
you had cancer?

35:20.844 --> 35:22.268
- I tried.

35:22.287 --> 35:23.787
- Well, how about grabbing me
by the shoulders

35:23.938 --> 35:25.438
and screaming it in my face?

35:25.457 --> 35:29.442
I know I'm self-obsessed, Cam,
but I'm your best friend.

35:29.461 --> 35:33.613
- Netty, I just didn't want you
to pity me.

35:33.632 --> 35:35.023
You already think of me

35:35.041 --> 35:37.859
as the lonely, loveless
cat lady.

35:37.878 --> 35:41.212
I couldn't handle being
the lonely, loveless cat lady

35:41.289 --> 35:43.974
with breast cancer
on top of it.

35:44.125 --> 35:48.961
- Oh, Cam,
that is so not how I see you.

35:48.981 --> 35:51.206
I know,
talk about lonely and loveless.

35:51.224 --> 35:52.540
I made my life seem perfect,

35:52.559 --> 35:56.969
but trust me, the honeymoon
was over years ago.

35:57.047 --> 36:00.231
You have no idea, do you,

36:00.308 --> 36:02.808
how jealous
I have always been of you?

36:02.828 --> 36:04.494
- What?
Come on.

36:04.646 --> 36:08.981
- Cam, you are magnetic.
You are beautiful.

36:09.075 --> 36:11.168
You live life
on your own terms.

36:11.319 --> 36:14.579
You see something you want,
and you go get it.

36:14.731 --> 36:16.581
<i> [soft music]</i>

36:16.733 --> 36:19.843
You were right when you said
that I need a man to define me.

36:19.994 --> 36:23.329
And I'm 50 years old.

36:23.348 --> 36:26.908
I have no idea what I want
or who I am,

36:26.910 --> 36:28.259
and that's
absolutely terrifying.

36:28.336 --> 36:30.245
And that's why this whole thing
breaks my heart

36:30.263 --> 36:34.065
because the real you is
so awesome.

36:36.010 --> 36:37.027
And it makes me angry to think

36:37.103 --> 36:41.198
that you need this body
to be happy.

36:43.017 --> 36:46.185
- Netty, do you remember
how you felt

36:46.263 --> 36:48.763
when you found out
about Paul's affair?

36:48.782 --> 36:51.599
- Yeah, I'd like to forget,
but yeah, angry, betrayed.

36:51.618 --> 36:54.878
- Yeah, that's how I feel
about my body now.

36:55.029 --> 36:58.364
I had this great life.

36:58.442 --> 37:01.701
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:01.778 --> 37:04.721
And my body betrayed me.

37:04.872 --> 37:07.724
And I just wanted out.

37:07.875 --> 37:09.968
- You wanted
to divorce your body?

37:09.970 --> 37:14.272
- I did.
Yeah, just for a few days.

37:15.883 --> 37:19.736
I just wanted
to feel whole again.

37:19.887 --> 37:23.240
And I miss my boobs.

37:23.316 --> 37:25.575
- They were great boobs.
- They really were.

37:25.727 --> 37:29.228
[both laugh]

37:29.306 --> 37:31.155
- I'm just so glad
we didn't lose you, Cam.

37:31.308 --> 37:32.807
I don't want to grow old
without you.

37:32.826 --> 37:34.976
- Me neither.

37:34.995 --> 37:42.259
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:45.989 --> 37:49.841
- I love you so much.

37:49.917 --> 37:51.493
- I love you too.

37:51.511 --> 37:58.441
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

37:59.427 --> 38:00.835
- Yes, hi.

38:00.854 --> 38:02.762
I would like to make an
appointment with Dr. Schwartz.

38:02.764 --> 38:04.114
As soon as possible, please.

38:04.265 --> 38:07.266
Claire, it's Margot Shear.
Good.

38:07.344 --> 38:08.860
I was wondering
if I could get the number

38:09.012 --> 38:11.604
of that trainer-nutritionist
woman you were raving about.

38:11.681 --> 38:12.789
<i> Gary, it's me.</i>

38:12.940 --> 38:15.033
I'm sending you an article.
Read it.

38:15.185 --> 38:16.868
It's about the mental load
of parenting.

38:17.020 --> 38:19.187
I'm gonna need you
to pick up 50% of this.

38:19.189 --> 38:20.964
You can choose which half,
but it's happening.

38:21.041 --> 38:22.690
June, this is Margot.

38:22.709 --> 38:25.209
I'm gonna need an assistant,
and this is not a negotiation.

38:25.286 --> 38:26.285
Assistant or I quit.

38:26.305 --> 38:29.380
Set reminder.
Put yourself first.

38:29.533 --> 38:32.309
<i> [upbeat music]</i>

38:32.460 --> 38:39.316
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

38:52.331 --> 38:54.222
[gasps]

38:54.224 --> 38:57.650
You're back.
- And here to stay.

38:57.669 --> 39:01.062
Just like you.
- Oh.

39:01.064 --> 39:03.081
- I don't want to see you
in a coffin again.

39:03.157 --> 39:05.991
- Okay.
- I'm sorry.

39:06.069 --> 39:09.754
We were selfish jerks.
- Horrid. Awful.

39:09.906 --> 39:12.182
- Inconsiderate
and self-centered.

39:12.258 --> 39:15.093
- Guys, it was
the wakeup call I needed.

39:15.245 --> 39:17.912
- We're gonna do this
more often.

39:17.931 --> 39:20.840
Twice a year.
- Definitely.

39:20.917 --> 39:23.935
And you're gonna
let us help you.

39:24.087 --> 39:25.436
We talked about it,

39:25.513 --> 39:29.699
and we're each gonna watch
the girls a weekend a month.

39:29.851 --> 39:31.350
- Guys, that's a lot.

39:31.428 --> 39:33.703
- It'll help
with my empty nest syndrome,

39:33.855 --> 39:36.539
when I'm not at my new job.

39:36.616 --> 39:37.949
- What new job?

39:38.101 --> 39:40.284
- I'm gonna intern
with girl boss here.

39:40.361 --> 39:42.103
I'm gonna figure out
what I want to do

39:42.122 --> 39:44.697
and who I want to be
in this next chapter.

39:44.716 --> 39:48.342
- Next chapter.
I like that.

39:48.344 --> 39:50.778
- 50 is not too old
to find yourself.

39:50.797 --> 39:52.889
- No, not when
you have friends.

39:52.966 --> 39:55.058
Cheers.
- Happy Birthday.

39:55.209 --> 39:56.968
- Happy birthday!
- Happy birthday to us!

39:57.120 --> 40:00.288
- 50!
- 50!

40:00.290 --> 40:02.957
- I apologize for bailing
on girls' night,

40:02.976 --> 40:04.216
not that you missed me.

40:04.236 --> 40:07.645
- [laughs]
- How did it go with Gina?

40:07.797 --> 40:10.240
- Oh, it was amazing!
- Oh.

40:10.316 --> 40:12.984
- Yes, yes,
we danced all night.

40:13.078 --> 40:16.154
- That's it?
You danced all night?

40:16.230 --> 40:19.674
- Well, and the worst
manicures ever.

40:19.676 --> 40:22.477
What?
- [laughs]

40:22.495 --> 40:26.164
So anything else?

40:26.316 --> 40:29.742
- Well, it could have been.
- Okay.

40:29.761 --> 40:34.305
- I think,
but I kind of chickened out.

40:36.601 --> 40:38.009
I told her I was married.

40:38.161 --> 40:41.604
- You are, and you're not.

40:41.756 --> 40:44.515
- But I still feel
like I am, you know?

40:44.517 --> 40:48.260
- I know, I know.
- Ugh. I don't know.

40:48.338 --> 40:52.840
I guess I just need
to do things in my own time.

40:52.859 --> 40:55.785
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

40:56.012 --> 40:59.772
- I had sex with Javier.
- Wow.

40:59.866 --> 41:02.200
- Mm-hmm.

41:02.352 --> 41:05.687
- And how do you feel
about that?

41:05.780 --> 41:07.705
- Um, fine.

41:07.782 --> 41:10.074
Yeah.

41:10.226 --> 41:11.784
- You know what's
happening here, right?

41:11.803 --> 41:12.952
- What?

41:13.029 --> 41:14.545
- Well, I hate
to break it to you,

41:14.698 --> 41:19.124
but we're friends.

41:19.202 --> 41:21.811
Solid friends.

41:21.963 --> 41:24.147
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

41:24.298 --> 41:27.650
- I guess we are.

41:27.727 --> 41:32.030
[both laugh]
